# --- Lock files: workspace members must not have their own ---
**/pnpm-lock.yaml
!pnpm-lock.yaml
# Workspace root Cargo.lock IS committed per project convention; only
# nested member/scaffold lockfiles are excluded here. The e2e/rust
# crate is its own workspace (own Cargo.lock); committing it pins
# transitive deps (e.g. alloc-no-stdlib) so CI cargo invocations
# resolve to the same versions used locally.
**/Cargo.lock
!/Cargo.lock
!/e2e/rust/Cargo.lock
!packages/ruby/ext/spikard_rb/Cargo.lock
# The Elixir NIF crate ships its Cargo.lock in the Hex source tarball
# (mix.exs files list) so the package compiles standalone on consumers.
!packages/elixir/native/spikard_nif/Cargo.lock

